nique blend of qualitative and quantitative guidance to two kinds of financial institutions: those that just need a little help in staying on the right side of complex fair housing regulations; and those that aspire to industry leadership in profitably and responsibly serving the unmet credit needs of diverse businesses and consumers in America''s emerging domestic markets." --Michael A. Stegman, PhD, The John D. and Catherine T. MacArthur Foundation, Duncan MacRae ''09 and Rebecca Kyle MacRae Professor of Public Policy Emeritus, University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill', DEFAULT, '58.39', '356', '2008-03-14', DEFAULT, 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=yzCSSOZ5U34C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Fair Lending Compliance')ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
